org.cougaar.planning.ldm.measure
Class GenericDerivative<N extends Measure,D extends Measure>

java.lang.Object
  org.cougaar.planning.ldm.measure.GenericDerivative<N,D>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable, Derivative, Measure
Direct Known Subclasses:
GenericRate
public class GenericDerivative<N extends Measure,D extends Measure>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, Derivative

Generic derivative - represents a fraction of any measure over any other, e.g. Volume/Duration would be equivalent to the current FlowRate class. Could also be other derivates like Volume/Area, etc.

See Also:
for the Measure/Duration shorthand that comes up a lot, Serialized Form

valueOf

public Measure valueOf(double value)
This is a rate in the common unit of the numerator, by the denominator. So for instance if this rate is 10 gallons/hr, valueOf (5) would be 5 liters/hour, since liters is Volume's common unit.
